gomodel:SYNGO_2259  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099699 replaced by GO:0097060" , "Rationale: Fi.g4: \"In RTN of P14 γ20/0 brain, staining for the γ3 subunit revealed prominent punctate IR, indicative of synaptically clustered receptors. Moreover, γ3 subunit staining was colocalized with the α3 subunit (Fig. (Fig.44a), the most abundant α subunit in the RTN (20), and with gephyrin (Fig. (Fig.44b). Thus, in γ20/0 RTN, the endogenous γ3 subunit appears to contribute to postsynaptic GABAA receptors containing the α3 subunit, thereby preventing the loss of GABAA receptor clusters.\"\n\nNotes:\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.\n- Authors claim localization to the postsynaptic specialization membran, but this data on itself does not show this. I have annotated to the less specific term 'integral component of synaptic membrane (GO:0099699)'.. Experimental description: \"Miniature inhibitory postsynaptic currents (mIPSCs) and currents evoked by pulse application of GABA were recorded with the whole-cell patch-clamp method applied to neocortical neurons from γ2+/+, γ20/0, and γ3tg/γ20/0 embryos cultured \"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2259" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

